3. Design Principles
3.1 Separation of Intelligence and Presentation

The Cinematic Engine must not control:

chess evaluation
move legality
strategic decisions

Those responsibilities belong to upstream intelligence engines.

The Cinematic Engine only interprets events.

Example:

Input:

{
"event":"queen_capture",
"importance":"high"
}

Output:

{
"scene":"queen_execution",
"camera":"close_up",
"emotion":"dominance"
}
