6. Engine Components
6.1 Event Classifier
Responsibility

Classifies chess events into cinematic categories.

Input:

{
move:"Qxh7+",
event:"capture",
check:true
}

Output:

{
category:"critical_attack",
severity:"high"
}
Supported Event Categories
Category	Description
movement	normal positioning
attack	offensive action
capture	elimination event
defense	blocking/protection
sacrifice	intentional loss
check	threat event
checkmate	final victory event
promotion	transformation event
blunder	tactical failure
comeback	reversal event
6.2 Combat Mapping Engine
Responsibility

Maps chess mechanics to combat actions.

Initial Mapping Table
Chess Action	Combat Interpretation
Pawn move	advance
Pawn capture	soldier strike
Knight move	dash movement
Knight fork	combo attack
Bishop move	ranged spell
Bishop capture	energy blade
Rook move	heavy charge
Queen move	ultimate ability
King move	defensive maneuver
Castle	tactical reposition
Promotion	transformation
